    "subtitle": "Key patterns in OPV, IPV, and Polio 3 coverage across regions and background characteristics.",
    "overview": "Polio coverage improved nationally from 2022 to 2025, but the biggest pattern is the drop from early to later doses and the wide regional spread in completion. In 2025, OPV 1 is 93.0, OPV 2 is 89.5, OPV 3 is 83.0, IPV 1 is 89.1, IPV 2 is 78.9, and Polio 3 is 83.3. Compared with 2022, OPV 3 and IPV 1 are higher, but the later-dose gap remains substantial, especially in lower-performing regions and among children without visible vaccination cards.",
